      <div rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211" type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
        <!-- 
Comments below by Csaba Kiss and Dániel Balogh (BD) are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion. 
-->
        <!-- 
Sircar, D.C. & Pāṇḍeya-Sarmā, L.P, 'Pīparḍūlā plates of Narendra',
Indian Historical Quarterly, vol XIX, pp.139-146
GIVEN IN MICHAEL'S MAP
=
Sircar, D.C. Select Inscriptions vol. 1. 1965. pp. 488-490.
I USED THE LATTER. CsK 
-->
        <div n="A" type="textpart">
          <head xml:lang="eng">Seal</head>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="1">
            <lb n="1"/>
            <l n="a">khaḍga-dhārā-jita-bhuvaḥ</l>
            <l n="b">śara<unclear>bhāt prā</unclear>pta-janmanaḥ</l>
            <lb n="2"/>
            <l n="c">nr̥pateś śrī-narendrasya</l>
            <l n="d">śāsanaṁ ripu-śās<unclear>i</unclear>na<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied></l>
            <!-- 
The emendation śāsinaḥ is valid provided that the reading of si is secure. Otherwise, śāsanaM should be preferable. The facsimile in Shastri is very unclear (the one in IHQ is worse), but there does seem to be an i-like mark over the character preceding the final na. 
-->
          </lg>
        </div>
        <div n="B" type="textpart">
          <head xml:lang="eng">Plates</head>
          <p><pb n="1v"/><lb n="1"/><g type="mangala"/> svasti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
śarabha-purān mahārāja-śrī-narendraḥ
<lb n="2"/>nanda-pura-bhogīya-śarkarā-padrake brāhmaṇā<lb break="no" n="3"/>dīn prativāsi-kuṭumbino bodhayati<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
<lb n="4"/>Eṣa grāmo rāhudevena sva-puṇyābhivr̥ddha<lb break="no" n="5"/>ye brāhmaṇa-vājasaney<sic>a-Ā</sic>treya-sagotra-
						<pb n="2r"/><lb n="6"/>svāmippāya<!-- 
L6. Sircar suggests the name Svāmippa is a vernacularised form of Svāmyātman. 
-->tāmra-śāsanenātisr̥ṣṭo mayā<lb break="no" n="7"/>pi ca A-cāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśya Ity anumodito
<lb n="8"/>yato bhavadbhir asya yathākālaṁ meya-
<lb n="9"/>hiraṇyādīnāṁ pratyāyānām upanayaḥ
<lb n="10"/>karttavyaḥ </p>
          <p>bhaviṣyataś ca bhoga-patīn abhinandayati
						<pb n="2v"/><lb n="11"/>pūrvva-datter anupālanāc chreyasā sambandhaḥ Ā<lb break="no" n="12"/>cchedāc ca pratya<choice>
              <sic>pā</sic>
              <corr>vā</corr>
            </choice>ya Ity anuprapaśyadbhir bhavadbhi<lb break="no" n="13"/>r asya grāmasyānupālanaṁ karttavyaM<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
<lb n="14"/>vyāsa-gītau cātra ślokāv udāharanti|
</p>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="1">
            <l n="a">pūrvva<lb n="15"/>-dattāṁ dvijātibhyo</l>
            <l n="b">yatnād rakṣa yudhiṣṭhira</l>
            <pb n="3r"/>
            <lb n="16"/>
            <l n="c">mahīṁ mahīmatāṁ śreṣṭha</l>
            <l n="d">dānāc chreyo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>nupālanaM</l>
          </lg>
          <lg met="anuṣṭubh" n="2">
            <l n="a"><lb n="17"/>ṣaṣṭiṁ varṣa-sahasrāṇi</l>
            <l n="b">svargge vasati bhūmi-daḥ</l>
            <lb n="18"/>
            <l n="c">ācchettā cānumantā ca</l>
            <l n="d">tāny eva narake vase<supplied reason="omitted">T</supplied></l>
          </lg>
          <p><lb n="19"/>pravarddhamāna-t<choice>
              <sic>ri</sic>
              <corr>r̥</corr>
            </choice>tīya-varṣasya mārgga-śi<lb break="no" n="20"/>ra-māsa-divase daśame<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
						<sic>utkīrṇṇāṁ</sic><!-- 
L20: FN "Read utkīrṇṇaṁ or utkīrṇṇā". 
-->śrīdatteneti</p>
        </div>
